summaries.short: With guidance from sneaker customizer Alexander John and DC Comics’ Jim Lee, the remaining designers take inspiration from The Suicide Squad’s iconic characters to craft head-to-toe streetwear looks fit for a superhero.
summaries.full: The Hype meets The Suicide Squad as the contestants flex their muscles in a daunting one-day challenge that sees them pulling from the film’s iconic characters for superhero-inspired looks. With guidance from sneaker customizer Alexander John and DC Comics’ Jim Lee, the designers tackle everything down to custom kicks - while hoping to steer clear of elimination.

As the contestants pour their passion into their work, trailblazer Angelo Baque helps hone their messaging - and later, legendary guest Co-Signer Bobby Hundreds spots a particularly inspiring design, leaving the Co-Signers with a difficult decision.

summaries.full: Victory is within reach as the semi-finalists channel their loved ones for looks inspired by the strong women in their lives. summaries.full: After exploring their new work studio, the designers face a blind critique of their sample racks in an unexpected first impressions challenge. Next, they're creating a classic streetwear look for A$AP Ferg with the promise of a sky-high prize - and a lesson in the importance of asking the right questions.
